      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be fully characterized and traceable to the COU operating envelope, including fluid properties, temperature, and hematocrit.",
      "rationale": "Test conditions are well documented for flow rate and rotational speed but hematocrit variability and temperature control documentation are incomplete. Achieved level 3 falls one gradation below the required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric with uncertainty bounds must be applied to all primary QoIs across all COU operating points.",
      "rationale": "Hemolysis index comparisons are provided at three of five operating points with qualitative agreement statements. No formal validation metric with combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds was applied. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI used in validation must be identical to the clinical decision QoI, with direct traceability to the absolute hemolysis threshold.",
      "rationale": "Normalized hemolysis index is used in validation whereas the clinical decision requires absolute hemolysis values. The mapping introduces an unquantified translation step. Achieved level 3 versus required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating conditions must match the COU device geometry and patient population operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Validation was conducted on the FDA generic pump geometry rather than the actual VAD device geometry. Geometric and hemodynamic differences between the generic pump and the target VAD introduce substantial relevance gaps. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
