      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented evidence that the model is used within its validated operating range by qualified personnel following documented procedures.",
      "rationale": "No formal use error assessment was conducted. Analyst qualification records and documented simulation execution procedures are absent from the submission package. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification for the chosen turbulence model, hemolysis constitutive law, and blood rheology model must be provided with evidence of applicability to the COU flow regime.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was not assessed. The SST k-omega turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model were selected without documented justification of their applicability to the VAD operating regime. Flagged as critical epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be characterized with probability distributions and their influence on hemolysis QoI quantified through formal uncertainty propagation.",
      "rationale": "Although Monte Carlo UQ was performed on a subset of geometric parameters, blood viscosity, hematocrit, and hemolysis model coefficients were treated as fixed nominal values. Comprehensive input uncertainty characterization was not completed. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental sample size must be statistically justified with power analysis; sample variability must be characterized and reported.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis measurements were obtained from a single test rig with n=3 replicates per operating point. No statistical power analysis was performed to justify sample size adequacy. Flagged as epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions and material properties used in the CFD model must be demonstrated to be equivalent to those measured in the validation experiment.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles were prescribed as uniform plug flow in the CFD model while the experimental setup used a peristaltic pump with non-uniform pulsatile inflow. The equivalency of these boundary conditions was not formally evaluated. Flagged as epistemic gap."
